> [!NOTE]
> The new talent system means most classes have a highly variable number of cooldown abilities worth monitoring, and not everyone is equally mindful of “negative space” cooldowns that are hidden when available—hence the additional layout options.

---
## How to change between Layouts

This release includes two different TMW Layouts and a variable number of TMW bars. To actually be able to switch between them smoothly, **activate the Clique profile for your spec as explained in the [[Install\|Install]] section.** As an additional note, if you wish to customize your clique keybinds, you should do them within the shipped profile to maintain these macros, to save yourself the trouble of having to copy them to a new profile.

Repeated from the [[Install\|Install]] page:

|Function   | Keybind   |
|------- | ----  |
|Classic Layout (Default) | Numpad_Minus|
|Merged Layout | Numpad_Plus|
|Use only one Main TMW bar (Default) | Numpad_Divide|
|Use Two TMW Main bars | Numpad_Multiply|

# 1-Bar vs. 2-Bar

Most classes in the game can still easily get by with one TMW bar, but a few builds have definitely become "2 Bar" builds - they just have a ton more abilities to pay attention to than they used to. That said, you don't **have to** use two bars, if you prefer not to.

# Layout 1: FahUI "Classic" (Default)
![M/l1.png](data:image/png;base64,)

### Minimalist layout intended for high level characters that only displays your utility abilities when they're on CD. Perhaps not wise for newcomers to a class or the game, but you can manage with big brain.

## `Throughput abilities are:
- For DPS... throughput, with the occasional healing spell for hybrids
- For tanks: damage, defensives, and healing abilities.
- For healers: damage and healing abilities.

## `Utility abilities are:`
- Everything not covered by throughput, including movement abilities, CC, and defensives for non tanks.

### The main difference is that utility abilities are displayed 100% of the time, which is ideal for a few situations: if you're unfamiliar with your utility cooldowns and forget they exist unless you can see them, or for low level characters, who don't have enough throughput abilities to fill out even one bar anyway.
